## 28. Nakamise Shopping Street (Kaminarimon)\n\n### 29. Kappabashi Street (Kappabashi Dogugai)\n\n### 30. Rainbow Bridge\n\n## What travelers are saying\n\n### Senso-ji, the Heart of Asakusa\n\n### Tranquility in Tokyo – If You Beat the Crowds\n\n### Stunning View\n\n### Iconic. The energy!\n\n### Fine Temple Complex with Lots of Shops\n\n### The spot for anime, manga and gaming enthusiasts\n\n### Beautiful observation tower in Tokyo.\n\n### Fun area to spend at least some time in, if you came to Tokyo to shop - this is it\n\n### Recommend a visit!\n\n### Worth a visit…or 2.\n\n### Interesting Tokyo too many surprises [...] ### Interesting Tokyo too many surprises\n\n### An adults only night time adventure. Go for a wander, people watch, get lost. It’s safe and worth a visit.\n\n### Tokyo’s vision of the future\n\n### The exhibition is ★★★★, the staff is ★★★\n\n### The immense central station of Tokyo\n\nTokyo\n\n# THE 10 BEST Tokyo Sights & Historical Landmarks\n\nTripadvisor\n\nThis is the version of our website addressed to speakers of English in the United States. If you are a resident of another country or region, please select the appropriate version of Tripadvisor for your country or region in the drop-down menu.\n\nResult number 1, relevance score: 0.23635799\n## Explore By Interest\n\nTokyo Sightseeing Bus Tours\n\nLandmarks\n\nParks & Gardens\n\nZoos & Aquariums\n\nTheme Parks\n\nBeach & Pool\n\nScience Museums\n\nEnjoying Tokyo’s Open-Air Spaces\n\nMuseums and Magic: Fun Tokyo Activities for the Whole Family\n\nNew Tokyo Landmarks near Shibuya and Shinjuku Stations\n\nTop-Notch Mt. Fuji Viewpoints in Tokyo: TOKYO SKYTREE, the Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building and Haneda Airport\n\nVR Vacations and Esport Adventures in Ginza, Asakusa and at Tokyo Tower\n\nTokyo’s best spots for kids to learn through play\n\nNew large-scale commercial facilities in Tokyo\n\nLooking forward to the opening of Azabudai Hills\n\nExperiencing authentic Japanese culture in Tokyo\n\nTokyo Esports Guide\n\nJapanese Baseball in Tokyo: Watching and Practicing a Whole New Ball Game\n\n## Landmarks [...] Search\n Listen\n Share this page;)\n\n  Share this page\n\n  + Facebook\n  + X (Twitter)\n  + Email;)\n  + Copy URL;)\n FAVORITES\n Menu;)\n\nMain content starts here.\n\n Visit Tokyo |\n EXPERIENCES |\n Best things to do in Tokyo tailored to your preferences |\n Top tourist attractions in Tokyo: the best sightseeing spots |\n Landmarks\n\n6_0099_17main\n\n# Landmarks\n\nExperience the most iconic sights of Tokyo\n\n## Impossibly tall towers, adorable dogs and busy crossings are just some symbols of the city.\n\nWith so many quintessential structures, streets, stations and scenery to see, you could spend a month in Tokyo and still have plenty left to visit. Big and bold, small and inconspicuous, classic or modern, how many will you discover?\n\n## Ideas\n\n## Explore By Interest\n\nTokyo Sightseeing Bus Tours [...] + Central Tokyo\n    - Ginza\n    - Akihabara\n    - Tokyo Station & Marunouchi\n    - Nihonbashi\n    - Tsukiji\n    - Kanda & Jimbocho\n    - Tokyo Dome & Around\n    - Kagurazaka\n    - Akasaka\n    - Shinbashi & Shiodome\n    - Hamamatsucho\n  + Eastern Tokyo\n    - Asakusa\n    - Ryogoku\n    - Skytree & Around\n    - Toyosu\n    - Kiyosumi Shirakawa\n    - Fukagawa\n    - Kasai\n  + Western Tokyo\n    - Shinjuku\n    - Shibuya\n    - Harajuku\n    - Aoyama & Omotesando\n    - Shimokitazawa\n    - Daikanyama\n    - Kichijoji\n    - Nakano\n    - Yoyogi\n    - Koenji\n    - Okubo\n    - Futako Tamagawa\n  + Southern Tokyo\n    - Odaiba\n    - Shinagawa & Tennozu\n    - Nakameguro\n    - Roppongi\n    - Azabu Juban\n    - Tokyo Tower & Around\n    - Todoroki Valley\n    - Ebisu\n    - Haneda & Around\n    - Jiyugaoka\n\nResult number 2, relevance score: 0.18616937\n1. Ghibli Museum – A magical dive into Japan’s most beloved animation studio.\n2. Karaoke in Tokyo – Wild, loud, and unexpectedly fun.\n3. Tokyo Skytree – Epic views from the tallest tower in the world.\n4. DisneySea – A one-of-a-kind Disney park with adult appeal.\n5. Senso-ji – Tokyo’s oldest and busiest Buddhist temple.\n6. Akihabara – Tech, anime, maid cafés, and sensory overload.\n7. Imperial Palace – Quiet gardens around Japan’s royal residence.\n8. Shibuya Crossing – The famous scramble—pure Tokyo chaos.\n9. Nikko day trip – Shrines, forests, waterfalls—just stunning.\n10. Kamakura day trip – Big Buddha and chill temple-town vibes.\n11. Hakone + Mt. Fuji – Mountains, hot springs, Fuji views. Done. [...] ### Alternative observation options in Tokyo\n\n Similarly, Tokyo Tower, painted bright orange and white to comply with international aviation safety, is another iconic structure that stands out in Tokyo's skyline.\n Other notable observation points in Tokyo's cityscape include Mori Tower in Roppongi Hills, an iconic landmark offering panoramic views and a unique cultural experience, contrasting with the Skytree's modern design and height.\n\n## 4. Spend a day at Tokyo DisneySea\n\nVisting DisneySea in Tokyo, Japan\n\nThis was actually great fun\n\nI highly recommend spending one of your Tokyo days at DisneySea, the only one of its kind globally. It’s literally the most unique place to visit in Tokyo. [...] And if you’re afraid you’re missing out on the real Disney magic, don’t be. Disney has a knack for turning employees into perpetually waving, smiling robots, and the sets are as magical as they can be, so you still get the whole experience just like you would in Disneyland.\n\n### DisneySea vs Disneyland Tokyo: What’s the difference?\n\nDisneySea is like Disneyland’s older cousin—a little more mature, and a little more obsessed with water.\n\nAttraction at Disney Sea in Tokyo, Japan\n\nCool building, right? The Tower of Terror!\n\nResult number 3, relevance score: 0.18133602\n### Senso-Ji Temple\n\nTokyo’s oldest Buddhist temple stands as a symbol of the city’s deep-rooted traditions and remains one of the most significant ones to this day. Legend says that two fishermen found a statue of Kannon, the Goddess of Mercy, in the Sumida River. When they repeatedly tried returning it and it continuously reappeared, the village chief recognized its holiness and turned his home into a shrine for the golden statue. Today, visitors from around the world continue to admire the temple’s stunning architecture and pay their respects to Kannon during their visit.\n\n### Imperial Palace & Gardens [...] ### Akihabara Electric TownAkihabara Electric Tow\n\nThis buzzing district is a must-see for tech lovers, packed with electronic stores, arcades, and manga and anime shops. Aside from shops, anime-related establishments such as maid and manga cafes allow visitors to fully immerse themselves in Japan’s pop culture scene. With an endless array of electronics, collectibles, and a look into the vibrant entertainment culture of Japan, Akihabara is sure to make an unforgettable experience for any traveler.\n\n## Travel Tips for Exploring Tokyo’s Attractions\n\nTo truly experience the best of Tokyo, make sure to balance your itinerary between historical landmarks and futuristic attractions. The following tips will help you craft your perfect itinerary! [...] Need help logging in?\n\n### Not Registered Yet?\n\n# A Guide to Tokyo’s Most Futuristic and Historic Attractions\n\nFrom its captivating temples to its neon-lit skyscrapers, Japan’s capital offers a fascinating journey through time. Tokyo is a city where ancient traditions and modernity coexist in perfect harmony, making it an ideal destination for all travelers. Join us in diving into the must-visit sites that showcase Tokyo’s unique mix of history and innovation, allowing you to experience the best of both worlds!\n\nTravel to Tokyo with ACIS\n\n## Historic Tokyo: A Journey Back in Time\n\n### Senso-Ji Temple\n\nResult number 4, relevance score: 0.15361294\nToday, Tokyo offers a seemingly unlimited choice of shopping, entertainment, culture and 