ename to search for, e.g. 'config.json'", 'type': 'string'}, 'directory': {'default': '.', 'description': 'Directory to start the recursive search from; defaults to the current working directory', 'type': 'string'}, 'fuzzy': {'default': True, 'description': 'If True, fall back to case-insensitive substring matching when no exact match is found', 'type': 'boolean'}}, 'required': ['name'], 'type': 'object'}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'search_file_contents', 'description': 'Search a file for a keyword or phrase.\n\n    Returns a list of dicts, each containing the matching line number, the\n    matching line itself, and the surrounding context lines.', 'parameters': {'properties': {'filepath': {'description': 'Path to the file to search within', 'type': 'string'}, 'term': {'description': 'Keyword or phrase to search for; matching is case-insensitive', 'type': 'string'}, 'context': {'default': 3, 'description': 'Number of context lines to include before and after each match', 'type': 'integer'}}, 'required': ['filepath', 'term'], 'type': 'object'}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'get_file_contents', 'description': 'Return the text contents of a file, truncated to approximately the value of token_limit (hard-coded in the function) tokens.', 'parameters': {'properties': {'file': {'description': 'file whose context to get; may include its filepath', 'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['file'], 'type': 'object'}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'write_markdown_file', 'description': 'Write markdown content to a timestamped file in the given directory, creating the directory if needed.', 'parameters': {'properties': {'directory': {'description': 'Path to the directory to write the markdown file into; relative or absolute', 'type': 'string'}, 'info_to_write': {'description': 'Markdown formatted text to write to the file', 'type': 'string'}, 'file_name': {'description': 'The name of the file to write to', 'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['directory', 'info_to_write', 'file_name'], 'type': 'object'}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'get_full_directory_information', 'description': 'Get information and statistics about contents of given directory.', 'parameters': {'properties': {'directory': {'description': 'Directory to get full information on', 'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['directory'], 'type': 'object'}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'parallel_internet_research_agent', 'description': 'Delegate one or more independent research sub-tasks to be searched and synthesized in parallel. \n    Use this instead of internet_research when the task can be split into multiple independent searches which will ultimately be synthesized.\n    This tool is never executed directly, but is intercepted by the router to tringger the fan-out pattern via Send.', 'parameters': {'properties': {'queries': {'description': 'Run multiple simultaneous standalone search queries for research to be done in parallel. Each item should be a full natural-language search statement or question, independent of the others. ', 'items': {'type': 'string'}, 'type': 'array'}}, 'required': ['queries'], 'type': 'object'}}}]}}
