. first 1000 tokens of text:\n# Agent Harness\n\nA CLI agent harness with MCP server support, built-in native tools, and pluggable LLM backends. It connects any supported LLM to external tools via the [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/) and in-process native tools, managing the agentic tool-use loop so the LLM can call tools, process results, and iterate toward an answer.\n\nThe harness itself contains no model logic — it orchestrates the connection between LLMs and tools.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Python 3.11+\n- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) package manager\n- Node.js/npm (only if using MCP servers that run via `npx`)\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```bash\n# One-shot query using Anthropic (default provider)\nexport ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="your-key"\nuv run agent-harness "What time is it?"\n\n# Interactive REPL\nuv run agent-harness\n\n# With a config file\nuv run agent-harness -c config.json\n\n# Override provider and model\nuv run agent-harness -p openai -m gpt-4o "Summarize this project"\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\nThe agent can be', 'role': 'tool', 'tool_call_id': 'call_019ee636709c70e0afc55a59'}, {'content': 'File ~/Scripts/fluentpy was unreadable or binary.', 'role': 'tool', 'tool_call_id': 'call_019ee63671097560afad69a8'}, {'content': '#!/bin/bash \nset -v\n\necho "The path to my home directory is: $HOME"\necho "The terminal type I am using is: $TERM"\n\necho "That is all!"\nset +v\n', 'role': 'tool', 'tool_call_id': 'call_019ee63671757dd3a2289949'}, {'content': '["tutorial.md", "examples"]', 'role': 'tool', 'tool_call_id': 'call_019ee63671d27ba3a9e964f8'}, {'content': 'File ~/Scripts/aitoolcall was unreadable or binary.', 'role': 'tool', 'tool_call_id': 'call_019ee636722c7fc28a0eb5c6'}], 'model': 'MiniMaxAI/MiniMax-M2.7', 'max_tokens': 8192, 'parallel_tool_calls': False, 'stream': True, 'tools': [{'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'internet_research', 'description': "Executes a web search using the a websearch client.\n\n    Use this tool to find up-to-date information on the web. \n    When calling this tool, you must pass the user's inquiry as a complete, \n    natural language sentence. Never convert the search intent into a concatenated \n    keyword string (e.g., do NOT pass 'best practices prompting LLM', \n    instead pass 'What are the best practices for prompting an LLM?').", 'parameters': {'properties': {'query': {'description': 'The full, complete, and unmodified conversational question. CRITICAL: Do NOT extract keywords, summarize, or truncate. Pass the exact natural language intent.', 'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['query'], 'type': 'object'}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'change_directory', 'description': 'Change the current working directory to the given path.', 'parameters': {'properties': {'directory': {'description': 'Path to the directory to change into; relative or absolute', 'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['directory'], 'type': 'object'}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'list_directory', 'description': 'List the names of all entries in the given directory.', 'parameters': {'properties': {'directory': {'anyOf': [{'type': 'string'}, {'type': 'null'}], 'default': None, 'description': 'Optional path. If not provided, lists the current directory.'}}, 'type': 'object'}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'get_working_directory', 'description': 'Return the absolute path of the current working directory.', 'parameters': {'properties': {}, 'type': 'object'}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'path_exists', 'description': 'Check whether a file or directory exists at the given path.', 'parameters': {'properties': {'target': {'description': 'Path to check; relative or absolute', 'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['target'], 'type': 'object'}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'list_files_recursive', 'description': 'List all files matching the glob pattern recursively under the given directory.', 'parameters': {'properties': {'directory'